70,IssuesEvent,2017-03-18 22:33:39+00:00,55258005,jopohl/urh,5690599,gustavecha,,,opened,Noisy spectrum analyzer start,[],[],0,"Hi,

I going through weekly test of URH 1.6.1.8 :)
In spectrum analyzer, with RTL-TCP device.

Once start button pressed, pretty high noise level quickly appears and then disappear. It cause a bad memory effect on the red part of the FFT.
Peak detection and visualisation afterwards is hard.
I think it's about the parameters sent to rtl-tcp (gain for instance) a bit late which cause this artefact at the beginning.

Is this possible to skip the x first sample sent by device ?
Or offer to user the possibility to clean the FFT memory while listening ?
Currently it's only possible to do so when spectrum analyzer is not listening.
",{},{}
83,IssuesEvent,2016-06-02 12:37:36+00:00,55258005,jopohl/urh,18219846,jopohl,,,closed,Attach decoding to blocks,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/jopohl/urh/labels/critical', 'name': 'critical', 'color': 'b60205'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/jopohl/urh/labels/discussion', 'name': 'discussion', 'color': '0e8a16'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/jopohl/urh/labels/feature', 'name': 'feature', 'color': '84b6eb'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/jopohl/urh/labels/useability', 'name': 'useability', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}]",[],0,"### Labelsets
* Labelsets usually determine a message type, whereby each message type can have different encodings in practice. Therefore combining decoding and labelsets may be ergonomical.
* Usability (GUI design) is questionable
- Decoding will normally chosen before thinking about labels

-> No

### Blocks
* GUI design is simpler than with labelsets
- [x] When several blocks with different encodings are selected, show ""..."" element in combobox.
- [x] When nothing is selected, ask for confirmation whether the encoding of all blocks should be changed. At least for 10+ blocks.

-> Yes",{},{}
