239,IssuesEvent,2018-01-29 20:02:32+00:00,5542710,gmr/queries,49469,gmr,,,closed,Add easy way to retrieve info about session state,"[{'id': 12359137, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/gmr/queries/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]",[],2,"I am using the TornadoSession with hundreds of queries and if somehow a result isn't freed, tracking it down is a nightmare. I put this together and was wondering if it would be useful to have in the core of the application (if there is a better way please let me know)

``` python

import queries


class MySession(queries.TornadoSession):

    def query(self, sql, parameters=None):
        self.sql = sql
        self.parameters = parameters

        return super(MySession, self).query(sql=sql, parameters=parameters)

    def info(self):
        info = []

        for pid, pool in self._pool_manager._pools.items():
            i = pool.idle_connections
            b = [pool.connections[k] for k in pool.connections
                 if pool.connections[k].busy]
            u = [pool.connections[k].used_by().sql for k in
                 pool.connections if pool.connections[k].busy]

            info.append({
                'pid': pid,
                'idle': len(i),
                'busy': len(b),
                'running_queries': u
            })

        return info

```

If you ever wanted info about the session, you'd just call `session.info()`
",{},{}
241,IssuesEvent,2017-02-27 14:32:50+00:00,1258258,gotcha/ipdb,756433,gnebehay,,,closed,"ipdb autocompleter should be able to use ""readlinelike"" completions","[{'id': 522663474, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/gotcha/ipdb/labels/Feature%20request', 'name': 'Feature request', 'color': 'c2e0c6', 'default': False}, {'id': 522482604, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/gotcha/ipdb/labels/IPython%20issue', 'name': 'IPython issue', 'color': '1d76db', 'default': False}, {'id': 522484306, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/gotcha/ipdb/labels/Waiting%20for%20upstream%20fix', 'name': 'Waiting for upstream fix', 'color': 'b60205', 'default': False}]",[],8,"It would be nice to have a configuration option for ipdb to have the autocompleter use the ""old style readlinelike"" completions.

