1631,IssuesEvent,2016-12-03 00:07:17+00:00,27283062,ktbyers/netmiko,899716,ktbyers,,,closed,delay factor for getting prompt too small,[],[],8,"I ran into some issue to get the prompt for hp switches. After I looked into the code for hp_procurve_ssh.py and base_connection.py and found out the reason. Even the code compared the global delay and default delay factor, but the delay is not passed to set_base_prompt() in hp_procurve_ssh.py. In the set_base_prompt(), it can only use the default value,which is 1 sec, as the parameter, and it only waits 0.1 seconds to get the prompt. In my case, the device takes a little longer than 0.1 to read the prompt. 

we can either change .1 to .5 or 1 to wait longer for get the prompt, or passing the delay to set_base_prompt after select_delay_factor.

Another thing I don't quite understand is why the select_delay_factor is not implemented in base_connection. it sounds like a basic feature for all kinds of devices",{},{}
