1696,IssuesEvent,2017-09-03 21:13:07+00:00,11380094,msiemens/tinydb,3173673,therden,,,opened,Documentation of list field methods is confusing,[],[],0,"Perhaps I'd have better luck if the more information about the referenced database were provided, but I can't figure out the Query-based approach shown in the documentation.

I had better luck with the list-based approach.  After some trial and error, I believe that I understand the following:

- The *Any()* method returns records whose specified field contains a list whose contents include a match for *at least one one* value in the supplied list.
- The *All()* method will return every record whose specified field contains a list whose contents include matches *for **every** value* in the supplied list.

The comment preceding the list-based example in the documentation inadvertently suggests that *All()* is synonymous with *Any()*.  A better comment might be

> \>\>\>  \# User's groups include both 'admin' and 'user'
",{},{}
