2091,IssuesEvent,2015-08-09 11:34:39+00:00,8313091,miso-belica/sumy,1072330,miso-belica,,,closed,IDF Calculation in lex_rank,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/miso-belica/sumy/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}]",[],2,"In lex_rank.py, what is the motivation for calculating IDF for a word, w, as: 
IDF(w) = N/k 
where 
N = total number of sentences in the document 
k = the number of sentences containing the word

It is my understanding that:
IDF(w) = log (D/k)
where 
D = the number of documents in the corpus
k = the number of documents containing w.  

Are you treating each sentence as its own document?  If so, shouldn't there be a log thrown in front?  
I love this project by the way, thank you so much!",{},{}
