2124,IssuesEvent,2016-05-25 15:16:52+00:00,38793780,nickoala/telepot,14248879,yewsiang,,,opened,Callback_query called after DelegatorBot session has expired,[],[],0,"Hi,
Thanks a lot for the framework, it has made my development process really enjoyable!
Sorry if I'm asking a question that has been addressed but I couldn't find relevant questions.

I'm trying to ask the user a question and then allow the user to give me replies via a callback_query from an inline keyboard. After receiving the user's replies, I would also like to send the user a message. However, it is possible for the user to reply only after long periods of time (say 3hours) but the session would have expired.

Before the session expires, clicking on the ""Some function"" inline keyboard button would have allowed the DelegatorBot to send a message to the user saying ""-- Your callback query has been called --"". However, after expiry, clicking the button has no effect. Using ""bot.sendMessage()"" doesn't seem to work as well.

Is there a way to solve this?

Below is an example of what I'm trying to do.

`class MyBot(telepot.helper.ChatHandler):
    def __init__(self, seed_tuple, timeout):
        super(MyBot, self).__init__(seed_tuple, timeout)
        self.sender.sendMessage(""-- Initialization --"")

    def on_chat_message(self, msg):
        self.sender.sendMessage(""-- On chat message --"")
        markup = InlineKeyboardMarkup(inline_keyboard=[
                     [InlineKeyboardButton(text='Some function', callback_data='mycallbackfunction')],
                     [dict(text='Link to Forum', url='https://core.telegram.org/')]
                 ])
        self.sender.sendMessage(""Some question for the user"", reply_markup=markup)

    def on_callback_query(self, msg):
        query_id, from_id, data = telepot.glance(msg, flavor='callback_query')
        if data == 'mycallbackfunction':
            self.sender.sendMessage(""-- Your callback query has been called --"")
            bot.answerCallbackQuery(query_id, text='Callback query called!')

bot = telepot.DelegatorBot(TOKEN, [
    (per_chat_id(), create_open(MyBot, timeout=10)),
])
bot.message_loop(run_forever=True)
`
Thanks so much for the help!",{},{}
2129,IssuesEvent,2016-01-13 21:37:55+00:00,38793780,nickoala/telepot,5993916,boxama,,,closed,Can't post photo without a photo file buffer,[],[],3,"I'm reading a file directly from a web source, so I've got its data as bytes.
