2441,IssuesEvent,2017-11-20 14:52:42+00:00,78549488,flomotlik/formica,132653,flomotlik,,,opened,Support Stack Sets,[],[],0,"Stack sets are a great way to manage the same resources across multiple accounts/regions. Formica should get support for them natively. They should be implemented as set of subcommands `formica stack-set XXX` separate from normal stack handling.

*  formica stack-set create

Creates a new StackSet with the template from the current folder

* formica stack-set remove

Remove the specified stack set

* formica stack-set update

Updates the template of an existing Stack-Set

Imho any action beyond that is better done through the awscli directly. Formica should really only concern itself with the template part of the stack-set, not with setting up which accounts/regions it gets deployed to unless we find a good reason for it. Imho that can be better done with pure AWSCLI as its a very simple command call and there is practically no upside to having this in Formica. AWSInfo could get a few more commands to better list stack sets, instances of the stacks and operations. I want to make sure we only implement the most necessary here. @ryansb thoughts?",{},{}
