2485,IssuesEvent,2016-05-29 00:35:56+00:00,41279279,jsvine/pdfplumber,761387,Kirkman,,,opened,Best approach for text that spans columns?,[],[],0,"I'm trying pdfplumber for the first time. I really like it!

Here's my question. I deal with a lot PDFs like [this one](http://www.franklinmo.net/newdata/election/GM4_16Results.pdf). I have figured out how to get pdfplumber to identify the curved boxes, crop the page to each of those boxes, and then run extract_table() on those crops.

It's working great, with one exception. The first line (or lines) are essentially a title/header, and they span the columns of the table. So extract_table() will break the first line(s) at each column. eg:

	[u'MERAMEC R-III SCHOOL', u'BOARD', u'MEMBER', None]

