3866,IssuesEvent,2016-09-20 16:34:54+00:00,7433211,jmcnamara/XlsxWriter,4891495,Ragora,,,opened,Issue with add_table,[],[],0,"add_table throws a misleading warning in the variant of add_table that uses integer columns and rows when the ranges are setup incorrectly.  Given this, an error is the expected output but the type of error has caused undue headaches on my part given that the error thrown tells me nothing about why it was actually failing.

This is on Python 2.7.6 using xlsxwriter 0.9.3 and Excel 2016.

Demo code:
```python

import xlsxwriter

workbook = xlsxwriter.Workbook(""test.xlsx"")
sheet = workbook.add_worksheet()
table = {""name"": ""Test"", ""data"": [], ""columns"": [ {""header"": ""One""} ]}

# The table range is incorrect, so an error should be thrown but the wrong one is thrown
sheet.add_table(0, 0, 1, 1, table)

workbook.close()
```

