4646,IssuesEvent,2018-06-12 12:24:08+00:00,5739134,b-ryan/powerline-shell,6278341,mateuszzz88,,,opened,gnome-terminal tab title is not updated to name@host,[],[],0,"With ubuntu-default .bashrc, gnome-terminal (and probably other consoles) update tab/window title to user@hostname. This is achieved by 
```
case ""$TERM"" in
xterm*|rxvt*)
    PS1=""\[\e]0;${debian_chroot:+($debian_chroot)}\u@\h: \w\a\]$PS1""
    ;;
*)
    ;;
esac
```
powerline-shell does not add this part. It can be either directly added to output of powerline-shell or installation note can be updated to contain:
```
function _update_ps1() {
    PS1=""\[\e]0;${debian_chroot:+($debian_chroot)}\u@\h: \w\a\]$(powerline-shell $?)""
}
```
",{},{}
