5061,IssuesEvent,2015-03-10 05:43:27+00:00,9376661,lorenzofox3/Smart-Table,2402022,lorenzofox3,,,closed,WIP toggle columns,[],[],1,"Hello,

I've made an attempt to create reusable toggle columns for smart table, the plunkr (click on the wrench icon to open the menu and show hide a column):

http://plnkr.co/edit/6SHVFH5a2xgz3JAqemt6?p=info

I would like to contribute to smart table, I think it extends the smart table plugin without providing to much overhead. ATM I'm not really that happy with the code mainly because I fear there are to many scopes/watches/directives just to toggle columns on or off. (the upside is that if you dont use it there wont be any additional performance penalty).

I did try to use css selectors and hide them with css classes but ran into issues. when using an external pipe function with a timeout the hide classes are removed when the collection is updated. Instead I used seperate small directives that would hide depending on their column state in the `hiddenColumns` array in the table state.

I've created a directive that can be used as a toggle menu (instead of adding a switch/button next to every header, this conflicted with the sort option so I preferred a different menu). Of course this can be styled to create a pop over style or menu.

Any feedback would be welcome, I know there are some issue like the usage of lodash for one `_.find` but with some feedback and help I think we can create a nice addition for smart table.",{},{}
