5108,IssuesEvent,2012-03-09 15:57:27+00:00,1060073,omab/django-social-auth,91022,omab,,,closed,Gathering more profile info with Google OAuth2,[],[],3,"Hi Matias.

I continued my investigation after our yesterday chat and finally managed to obtain additional info from subj.

That's code I was using:

```python
from social_auth.backends import google

google.GOOGLEAPIS_EMAIL = ""https://www.googleapis.com/oauth2/v1/userinfo""

def googleapis_email(url, params):
    """"""A bit of hacking""""""
    from urllib2 import Request, urlopen
    from django.utils import simplejson
    
    request = Request(url + '?' + params, headers={'Authorization': params})
    try:
        return simplejson.loads(urlopen(request).read())
    except (ValueError, KeyError, IOError):
        return None

google.googleapis_email = googleapis_email
```

The key differences: you need to pull another url and do not check the body part of response, all data is already in root element of response.

I don't know how to implement that in way to allow DSA users to decide what to pull from GOAuth2. Any ideas?",{},{}
