6710,IssuesEvent,2017-08-21 03:35:32+00:00,31625947,PhilipGarnero/django-rest-framework-social-oauth2,11218556,ammarkhann,,,opened,Not sure what to pass in the parameters when fetching data?,[],[],0,"In my iOS app with my backend as Django. I log in my user from my friend with Facebook. It provides me with an access_token which I then send to my backend to get another token for the specific user.
``
        let userToken = FBSDKAccessToken.current().tokenString

        let params = [""grant_type"": ""convert_token"",""client_id"": client_id, ""client_secret"": client_secret , ""backend"": ""facebook"" , ""token"": userToken]

        Alamofire.request(self.baseUrl, method: .post, parameters:params, encoding: JSONEncoding.default).response { response in
            print(""Request: \(response.request)"")
            print(""Response: \(response.response)"")
            print(""Error: \(response.error)"")
            
            if let data = response.data, let utf8Text = String(data: data, encoding: .utf8) {
                print(""Data: \(utf8Text)"")
            }      }  ``


After that as the documentation says the exchanged token we get from our backend has to be passed on all the requests we perform further for the user. Now the problem I am facing is that I am unable to pass that token in my request. In **POSTMAN** I request the url with parameters being 
""Authorization"": ""Bearer token"" and it works. Inside my application when I request the same url with the following headers and parameters being nil (using Alamofire) it returns me that credentials were not provided. I have tried the same passing in parameters and it fails to fetch data. I have tried with the key being token , access_token and value being my actual token. It fails. Can anyone please guide me on this?

I have also posted the question over here where you can see the screenshot and the error in detail.
[https://stackoverflow.com/questions/45724551/can-not-fetch-data-using-alamofire/45726523?noredirect=1#comment78535674_45726523)](
",{},{}
