7229,IssuesEvent,2015-10-19 17:05:48+00:00,23458977,facebook/facebook-python-ads-sdk,5580170,rituparnamukherjee,69631,facebook,closed,"excessive "","" characters in the Insights.Field class (in the objects.py file)",[],[],1,"When migrating to the v2.5 of the SDK, I noticed strange error in my unit tests:
```
KeyError: ""('inline_link_clicks',)""
```

As it turned out, the error appears due to the "","" characters that are present after a couple of entries of the Insights.Field class (i.e. cost_per_inline_link_click, cost_per_inline_post_engagement, inline_link_clicks, inline_post_engagement). Because of the "","" characters, those entries are treated as tuples instead of strings. 

Those "","" characters should probably be removed, right? Or am I missing something.

Greetings
  Marko Novak
",{},{}
