8841,IssuesEvent,2017-12-13 12:27:47+00:00,82182681,openshift/openshift-restclient-python,79151,joshbenner,792337,openshift,opened,Client changes types when parsing IntOrString,[],[],0,"When deserializing, the client parses values that swagger defines as `io.k8s.apimachinery.pkg.util.intstr.IntOrString` as only a string. This causes problems if you read an object, modify, then try to re-upload it in some cases.

Specifically, I hit this when reading a deployment, adding an attribute, and updating it (via ansible.kubernetes-modules). My strategy.rolling_update.max_surge in Kubernetes is integer `1`, but when the client deserializes, it coerces that value to a string. When that is then sent back to k8s, I get an error because if maxSurge is a string, it should have a `%` character at the end.",{},{}
