9160,IssuesEvent,2015-09-08 05:11:00+00:00,9252533,numenta/nupic,15566,rhyolight,1039191,numenta,opened,nupic.__version__ missing,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic/labels/priority:1', 'name': 'priority:1', 'color': 'e11d21'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic/labels/subject:api', 'name': 'subject:api', 'color': 'c7def8'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic/labels/type:bug', 'name': 'type:bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}]",[],0,"The imported `nupic` module in python used to have a `__version__` attribute. This was assumed to be a part of the public API, so `nupic.studio` depends on it. At some point in the last few months, this attribute has gone missing.

```
> python
Python 2.7.6 (default, Sep  9 2014, 15:04:36)
[GCC 4.2.1 Compatible Apple LLVM 6.0 (clang-600.0.39)] on darwin
Type ""help"", ""copyright"", ""credits"" or ""license"" for more information.
>>> import nupic
>>> nupic
<module 'nupic' from '/Users/mtaylor/Library/Python/2.7/lib/python/site-packages/nupic.bindings-0.1.5-py2.7-macosx-10.9-intel.egg/nupic/__init__.pyc'>
>>> nupic.__version__
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""<stdin>"", line 1, in <module>
AttributeError: 'module' object has no attribute '__version__'
```

Unless someone thinks otherwise, I feel like this should be treated as an inadvertent API breakage and labeled `priority:1`. Especially because it was [reported on the mailing list](http://lists.numenta.org/pipermail/nupic_lists.numenta.org/2015-September/011608.html). 

It should be pretty easy to add back, hopefully? ",{},{}
