9882,IssuesEvent,2016-06-13 15:24:00+00:00,2527828,getsentry/raven-python,1538458,alexkiro,1396951,getsentry,opened,Memory optimization `pkg_resources` ,[],[],0,"Raven is currently using some excess memory on import that could be improved. A simple script using [memory_profiler](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/memory_profiler) and using `Python 3.5`:

```python
from memory_profiler import profile

@profile
def test():
    import raven

if __name__ == '__main__':
    test()
```

Shows 10.3 MB used after import:

```
Line #    Mem usage    Increment   Line Contents
================================================
     3     13.6 MiB      0.0 MiB   @profile
     4                             def test():
     5     23.9 MiB     10.3 MiB       import raven
```

I traced down all the standard and third-party imports of raven and these are the ones that are adding the extra memory:

```
     5     13.8 MiB      0.3 MiB       from datetime import datetime
     6     14.8 MiB      1.0 MiB       from hashlib import md5
     7     17.6 MiB      2.7 MiB       from http import client as httplib  # NOQA
     8     18.2 MiB      0.7 MiB       from unittest import TestCase as BaseTestCase  # NOQA
    10     21.0 MiB      2.8 MiB       import pkg_resources
    11     23.6 MiB      2.6 MiB       import requests
```

It doesn't seem like `pkg_resources` is required for normal usage of raven, so I suggest getting rid of this extra overhead. After removing the import:

```
Line #    Mem usage    Increment   Line Contents
================================================
     3     13.5 MiB      0.0 MiB   @profile
     4                             def test():
     5     13.5 MiB      0.0 MiB       import sys
     6     13.5 MiB      0.0 MiB       sys.modules[""pkg_resources""] = None
     7     20.9 MiB      7.4 MiB       import raven
```

-----

Other notes:

- I'll open a separate issue for the unittests
- The rest of the of the imports seem common enough so I don't it's worth optimizing
",{},{}
