10344,IssuesEvent,2018-03-27 04:19:06+00:00,3470471,FortAwesome/Font-Awesome,1669373,nickgrealy,1505683,FortAwesome,opened,"""How to use"" documentation incorrectly uses `fas` class in examples",[],[],0,"### Describe the problem

""How to use"" documentation incorrectly uses `fas` as a classname in the examples.

e.g.
```html
<i class=""fas fa-camera-retro""></i>
```
https://fontawesome.com/how-to-use/svg-with-js#how-it-works

### What did you expect?

I expected an image of a camera icon to show. Instead, I received a square box (i.e. the icon was not found).

When I changed the class name to `fa`, the icon showed correctly.

i.e.
```html
<i class=""fa fa-camera-retro""></i>
```

**Answer:** https://stackoverflow.com/a/21815998/782034

### What version and implementation are you using?

Version: `""font-awesome"": ""4.7.0""`
Browser and version: `Chrome Version 65.0.3325.181 (Official Build) (64-bit)`

- [ ] SVG with JS
- [x] Web Fonts with CSS
- [ ] SVG Sprites
- [ ] On the Desktop

### Reproducible test case

http://jsbin.com/gerekoq/edit?html,output

### Bug report checklist

- [x] I have filled out as much of the above information as I can
- [x] I have included a test case because my odds go _way_ up that the team can fix this when I do
- [x] I have [searched for existing issues](https://github.com/FortAwesome/Font-Awesome/issues) and to the best of my knowledge this is not a duplicate**

** similiar...
- https://github.com/FortAwesome/Font-Awesome/issues/12692 - not properly completed issue
- https://github.com/FortAwesome/Font-Awesome/issues/12654 - relates to FontAwesome5 (not `4.7.0`)",{},{}
10356,IssuesEvent,2018-07-08 07:52:00+00:00,3470471,FortAwesome/Font-Awesome,556268,tagliala,1505683,FortAwesome,closed,Icon request: geolocate (locate / geolocation),[],[],1,"### What can it be used for?

Buttons to enable browser geolocation, relating to an address that's been previously geolocated, etc.

