10584,IssuesEvent,2015-09-24 23:40:45+00:00,15510233,openfisca/openfisca-france,6614121,adrienpacifico,1794404,openfisca,closed,raw_decote and true_decote ?,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/openfisca/openfisca-france/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'cc317c'}]",[],1,"Decote is now calculated for ip_net, such that if it is substracted to ir_plaf_qf. Decote is positive (and maximum) for household that have income below the first IR tax threshold, that should not be the case. When you compare to the DGFIP website decote thus overcalculated for household that do not pay irpp since for the simulator is giving only the fiscal gain due to the decote mechanism.

We could calculate afterwards a true_decote (and rename decote as raw_decote) as :

```
@reference_formula
class true_decote(SimpleFormulaColumn):
    column = FloatCol(default = 0)
    entity_class = FoyersFiscaux
    label = u""Décote après calcul de l'impôt""
    start_date = date(2002, 1, 1)

    def function(self, simulation, period):
        period = period.start.offset('first-of', 'year').period('year')
        decote = simulation.calculate('decote', period)
        ir_plaf_qf = simulation.calculate('ir_plaf_qf', period)

        return period,  0*(ir_plaf_qf <= 0) + (ir_plaf_qf - decote) * (ir_plaf_qf > 0)
```

What do you think ? There might be a more efficient solution by coding decote directly, but it might not be the best thing to do.",{},{}
