 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/fpagnoux/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}, {'login': 'edarin', 'id': 20658648, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/20658648?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/edarin', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/edarin', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/edarin/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/edarin/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/edarin/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/edarin/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/edarin/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/edarin/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/edarin/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/edarin/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/edarin/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"Following a question from Robert Cauneau, we've noticed that some input variable can't be divided into months.

cf : https://jupyter.openfisca.fr/notebooks/users/robert/Etudes%20de%20variables/Test_Retraite_divided.ipynb.

For example: the `retraite_brute`    
But the problem is that some variables are based upon this one (as `csg_deductible_retraite`) and that these variables are calculated on a monthly basis. So there are every time put to zero.

Looking at the code, I think that only one line is missing in the definition of `retraite_brute` in comparison to other variables` :   
`set_input = set_input_divide_by_period`.

Ths issue concerns at least : `retraite_brute`, `chomage_brut`

But also all monthly variables that you want to add as entry variable in the init_single_entity method.
",{},{}
