11029,IssuesEvent,2015-02-01 01:01:42+00:00,16316451,GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python,520669,dhermes,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,opened,Remove __iter__ and __contains__ from Connection in storage,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python/labels/storage', 'name': 'storage', 'color': 'bfe5bf'}]",[],0,"@tseaver WDYT?

This is part of a movement towards making `Connection` more of a background / low-level / raw interface (like it is for datastore).

What's more

```python
for bucket in connection.get_all_buckets():
    ...
```

seems much more clear than

```python
for bucket in connection:
    ...
```",{},{}
