11858,IssuesEvent,2017-08-01 19:26:46+00:00,49976939,learningequality/kolibri,374612,benjaoming,3926525,learningequality,opened,"Make ""make dist"" more robust",[],"[{'login': 'benjaoming', 'id': 374612, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/374612?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/benjaoming', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"## Summary

These are issues and suggestions from building and releasing 0.4.4 on PyPi:

Since the build environment is going to invoke a runtime kolibri environment (which is not really ideal, but at this point hard to fix), we should ensure that we don't build on unclean environments. This has the potential to mess up static assets (mixing in things from from different versions).

 - [ ] Ensure running in a virtualenv?
 - [ ] Create and activate a new virtualenv?
 - [ ] Use a unique, temp KOLIBRI_HOME
 - [ ] Uploads should happen with twine
 - [ ] Consolidate Make routines across all branches, so we don't slip up if we do releases in old branches

Notice that it's **NOT** an advantage to have completely clean build systems if they are very slow.",{},{}
