11925,IssuesEvent,2016-08-16 10:30:49+00:00,8684396,trezor/cython-hidapi,8298277,mmortal03,4146447,trezor,opened,Can't install cython-hidapi within cygwin (sys.platform selection logic in setup.py doesn't account for it),[],[],0,"I've been trying to install cython-hidapi on Windows within cygwin, and ran into the following error:

> $ pip install hidapi
> Collecting hidapi
>   Using cached hidapi-0.7.99.post17.tar.gz
>     Complete output from command python setup.py egg_info:
>     Traceback (most recent call last):
>       File ""<string>"", line 1, in <module>
>       File ""/tmp/pip-build-W1qbyY/hidapi/setup.py"", line 86, in <module>
>         ext_modules = modules,
>     NameError: name 'modules' is not defined
>     ----------------------------------------
> Command ""python setup.py egg_info"" failed with error code 1 in /tmp/pip-build-W1qbyY/hidapi/


It looks like the cause is that the sys.platform selection logic in setup.py doesn't account for Cygwin's sys.platform string being ""cygwin"".

Replacing line 44 with the following seems to work around the issue (if, indeed, a cygwin install should be treated the same as Windows), though I haven't been successful with having it actually detect a device yet:

if (sys.platform.startswith('win')) or sys.platform.startswith('cygwin'):",{},{}
11937,IssuesEvent,2015-12-09 07:24:01+00:00,27823188,aldryn/aldryn-newsblog,270307,FinalAngel,4201738,aldryn,closed,Request For Documentation - Overriding default template,[],[],7,"Hi,

Context
----------
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;I'm using a fresh install of django-cms with aldryn-newsblog. Everything is working really fine.

Problem
----------
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Now that everything is working, i would like to customize the look and feel of this new blog engine.
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;I can override css as usual with bootstrap, but i want to dig a bit further and modify the base template.
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;I can't figure out how i can override the default template for aldryn_newsblog.

What I've tried
------------------
* Create a new `project/templates/aldryn_newsblog` folder and put modifiy `base.html` inside.
* Ensure that `django.template.loaders.filesystem.Loader` is loaded before `app_directories.Loader` and before `aldryn_boilerplates`
* I understand `aldryn_newsblog` use `aldryn_boilerplates` and i've read the docs for aldryn_boilerplates as well. You explain how to integrate boilerplate in a new app but not how we can override/extend the base boilerplate.


What I want
---------------
* Is this a stupid idea to do that ? Can i achieve that ?
* The documentation should clearly state if we can override base template (as we can with any other django app) and how we can do it.


