12287,IssuesEvent,2016-09-13 13:33:58+00:00,41092776,superdesk/superdesk-core,179249,petrjasek,5527298,superdesk,closed,Superdesk Caching,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/superdesk/superdesk-core/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}]",[],1,"we need caching in superdesk to keep performance under load. Lets gather requirements and do some research before implementing:

### Requirements
- cache db/elastic queries
- cache file reading/parsing
- share cache between requests/celery workers
- invalidating cache by tag
- per request/session cache

### Required Backends
- Redis
- Memcached

### Libraries
- Flask-Cache
- Werkzeug cache module
- Hermes
- Beaker

## API

there should be a decorator for caching, something like:

```
from superdesk.cache import cache

@cache(ttl=600)
def do_something(foo):
    ...

class CachedService(Service):

    @cache(ttl=30, tags=['activity'])
    def get_activity(self, user_id):
        ...
```

this way we can wrap db/elastic/etc calls and cache it.

Pls let me know what other requirements/libs/etc you can think of and I will look into it and evaluate.
/cc @mugurrus @jerome-poisson @ioanpocol @mdhaman @akintolga @marwoodandrew @hlmnrmr",{},{}
