12572,IssuesEvent,2016-01-21 21:04:29+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,1360539,bacongobbler,6117407,deis,closed,Support multiple store-gateways running simultaneously,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/deis/deis/labels/store%20(Ceph)', 'name': 'store (Ceph)', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}]",[],2,"Both the `registry` and `database` components use the `store-gateway` to store their persistent data. With a large amount of data, we've seen the gateway fall over in some cases (#3479). We implemented multiple gateways in #2929, but there is a `masterLock` mechanism which ensures only one is serving traffic at any one time.

We should investigate supporting multiple gateways running at once. This involves removing the `masterLock` logic, changing the host/port publishing path of the components, and changing `router` to template multiple gateway upstreams.

Some considerations:
- Does it cause problems that all of the containers use the same hostname (`deis-store-gateway`)?
- Is there a possible conflict if the registry and database are talking to different gateways, but modifying the same objects in Ceph via the S3 API?",{},{}
