12680,IssuesEvent,2017-07-24 09:23:45+00:00,71996613,blue-yonder/tsfresh,13162426,MaxBenChrist,6234170,blue-yonder,closed,Development roadmap,[],[],5,"We should have a discussion about the development roadmap for tsfresh:

I would propose that we focus on the speed in the near future. 

1. Getting the parallelization right (chunk size?)
2. maybe caching some feature calculators
3. doing some performance testing with the different feature calculators (see issue #74), maybe speed up some
4. increase number of unit tests (issue #11)
5. get the impute function faster (issue #123)

Then we should have some discussions about the data flow internally. For example @jneuff raised some issues with the current state of the extraction settings object and I agree with him. We should improve on that.

After we cleaned our internal data flow, we should improve the documentation (issues #92, #102, #61, #51 and so on)

Then, when we have finished that we can tackle topics like statefull feature calculators, new feature calculators, rolling time window functionality and so on.

",{},{}
12709,IssuesEvent,2017-12-26 22:42:53+00:00,77478378,ethereum/py-evm,824194,pipermerriam,6250754,ethereum,closed,Rename EIP150 fork to Tangerine Whistle,"[{'id': 631592722, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ethereum/py-evm/labels/Good%20First%20Issue', 'name': 'Good First Issue', 'color': '0e8a16', 'default': False}]",[],0,"### What is wrong?

The `evm.vm.forks.eip150` should really be named `evm.vm.forks.tangerine_whistle` to conform to the current naming convention for the fork modules.

### How can it be fixed

Rename the module and all of the various places where imports happen from that module, as well as anything that's named as EIP150 which isn't specific to the actual EIP150 rules but rather refers to the fork.
",{},{}
