12871,IssuesEvent,2017-05-09 08:42:36+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,1418419,kalefranz,6392739,conda,closed,Unsatisfiable package hints in conda build aren't very helpful,"[{'id': 91066590, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/conda/conda/labels/1%20-%20Backlog/long%20term', 'name': '1 - Backlog/long term', 'color': 'FFFFFF', 'default': False}, {'id': 75417446, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/conda/conda/labels/priority:low', 'name': 'priority:low', 'color': 'cccccc', 'default': False}, {'id': 450740657, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/conda/conda/labels/tag:solver-messaging', 'name': 'tag:solver-messaging', 'color': 'c5def5', 'default': False}]",[],3,"If you conda build a package that has unsatisfiable runtime dependencies (like you build it for Python 3 but one of the runtime dependencies does not have a Python 3 version), then you just get `RuntimeError: Unsatisfiable package specifications
Hint: <the package you just built> has a conflict with the remaining packages`

Aside from the fact that you get a traceback, the hint is not very helpful, because it doesn't tell you what you really want to know, which is what the problem with your runtime dependencies is. 

