13009,IssuesEvent,2016-06-06 20:17:48+00:00,16557526,pysam-developers/pysam,4426336,AndreasHeger,6598771,pysam-developers,opened,Fetching from a CRAM file fails if multiple_iterators is False,[],[],0,"The following fails for CRAM files, but works for BAM files:

```python
        for a, b in zip(samfile1.fetch(contig, start, stop,
                                       multiple_iterators=False),
                        samfile1.fetch(contig, start, stop,
                                       multiple_iterators=True)):
            self.assertEqual(a.compare(b), 0)
```

while the following works in both cases:

```python
        for a, b in zip(samfile1.fetch(contig, start, stop,
                                       multiple_iterators=False),
                        samfile1.fetch(contig, start, stop,
                                       multiple_iterators=True)):
            self.assertEqual(a.compare(b), 0)
```

See AlignmentFile_test.py testDoubleFetchCRAMWithRegion.



",{},{}
