13164,IssuesEvent,2018-01-04 21:41:28+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,5723682,tjprescott,6844498,Azure,closed,Prevent breaking changes within azure.common,"[{'id': 660632322, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/azure-cli/labels/Knack', 'name': 'Knack', 'color': 'f1f1f1', 'default': False}, {'id': 418935058, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/azure-cli/labels/P1', 'name': 'P1', 'color': 'b60205', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'tjprescott', 'id': 5723682, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/5723682?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tjprescott', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/tjprescott', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tjprescott/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tjprescott/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tjprescott/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tjprescott/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tjprescott/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tjprescott/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tjprescott/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tjprescott/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tjprescott/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",1,"The Knack-based core made changes to certain methods that are utilized by the azure.common package, resulting in breaking changes. These changes were needed because the Knack-based core needs a CLI context to work.

- [x] _profile.py Profile constructor
- [x] get_active_cloud method

The fix for these cases will be to make cli_ctx an optional parameter which, if not supplied, will be created for the duration of the call.  Alternatively, the affected azure.common methods could be altered to create a CLI context and pass that. 

cc/ @annatisch @lmazuel @mayurid 
  
  ",{},{}
13165,IssuesEvent,2017-03-10 22:09:12+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,3990654,rickrain,6844498,Azure,opened,Add support for 'OptionalParameters' to group deployment create|validate ,[],[],0,"foThere needs to be a way to pass optional parameters to a group deployment, while at the same time passing in `--template-file <path tot template file>` and `--parameters @<path to template parameters file>`.

The Azure SDK tools build on the notion of passing in `_artifactsLocation` and `_artifactsLocationSasToken` parameters in the template file you would pass in the` --template-file` parameter for az group deployment create|deploy.  The precedent that has been set is for these values to be configured dynamically, which the Azure SDK team has done elegantly in the PowerShell script they produce as part of an Azure Resource Group project in Visual Studio. 

To deploy templates that have been developed using the Azure SDK tools, support for an array of optional parameters is needed.  For example,

`az group deployment create --resource-group $RSRC_GRP_NAME --template-file $TEMPLATE_FILE --parameters ""@${TEMPLATE_PARAMETERS_FILE}"" ${optional-parameters}`




",{},{}
