13183,IssuesEvent,2017-11-03 02:46:19+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,10146011,JasonRShaver,6844498,Azure,closed,Show commands return zero rather than an error code,[],[],1,"If show commands return zero rather than an error code when an entity does not exist, they can be used as ""exists"" in scripts.

This is also useful in scripts which use `set -e`, since returning non-zero in this case would cause the whole script to exit.

This also enables the following flow, which is very helpful since some of the idempotent creates take a _long_ time even when everything has already been created.
```bash
NAME=$(az vmss show -g ${RESOURCE_GROUP} -n ${NAME} --query ""name"" -o tsv)
if [ -z ${NAME} ]; then
    # do something with the name
else
    # do something if the entity does not exist
fi
```",{},{}
13187,IssuesEvent,2018-03-14 23:36:14+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,1329240,troydai,6844498,Azure,opened,[Storage] The encryption key parameters are missing from storage account update command.,[],[],0,"Three parameters are missing from `az storage account update` command, which impacts the storage customer managed key scenario.
```
    --encryption-key-name   : The name of the KeyVault key.
    --encryption-key-vault  : The Uri of the KeyVault.
    --encryption-key-version: The version of the KeyVault key.
```
This is a regression introduced during knack conversion.",{},{}
