13551,IssuesEvent,2018-02-14 10:08:58+00:00,13258039,aio-libs/aiohttp,356399,asvetlov,7049303,aio-libs,opened,Accept a coroutine in web.run_app,"[{'id': 58986077, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/aio-libs/aiohttp/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 344996043, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/aio-libs/aiohttp/labels/server', 'name': 'server', 'color': '006b75', 'default': False}]",[],0,The proposal allows to execute async IO before creating an application,{},{}
13553,IssuesEvent,2017-11-24 10:37:41+00:00,13258039,aio-libs/aiohttp,356399,asvetlov,7049303,aio-libs,opened,Implement set_result and set_exception helpers,[],[],0,"The intention is replacement code like
```
   if not waiter.done():
       waiter.set_result(result)
```
with just `set_result(waiter, result)`
The same for `set_exception(waiter, exception)`.
I believe the change will make aiohttp code more robust.

Other effect is better test coverage.
`if not waiter.done()` check is used in very nested calls, it's extremely hard to write unit tests for the case. Very often the test could be done by `mock` usage only. Helpers could simplify testing a lot.",{},{}
