14191,IssuesEvent,2016-12-05 20:17:08+00:00,68969764,BD2KGenomics/toil-vg,10113932,cmarkello,8701293,BD2KGenomics,closed,IOStore directory compression slow,[],[],0,"We know moving files around is going to be a bottleneck that needs tuning.  One thing that jumps out at me while testing on chr22 is how much time it takes to gzip directories when writing via the IOStore interface.  

For example, 
https://github.com/BD2KGenomics/toil-vg/blob/master/src/toil_vg/vg_index.py#L240-L241
takes about as much wall time as the indexing itself.  

Immediate fix is to turn off compression here (maybe by adding an option to write_global_directory).  vg and index files are already compressed anyway.   

",{},{}
