14197,IssuesEvent,2016-02-17 21:01:43+00:00,39923176,BD2KGenomics/toil-scripts,7423296,jpdna,8701293,BD2KGenomics,opened,OSError reported by bwa_alignment.py toil script,[],[],0,"We are trying to run:

https://github.com/fnothaft/toil-scripts/blob/adam-vs-gatk-heuermh/src/toil_scripts/adam_gatk_pipeline/call_vs_grch38.sh

on a cluster created as so:
cgcloud create-cluster --zone us-west-2a --cluster-name justin-adam-gatk --num-workers 2 --instance-type r3.8xlarge --ebs-volume-size 100 toil

and specifically, I changed toil invocation command line in call_vs_grch38.sh  to use a  larger test file input fastq at:
--s3_bucket s3://paschall-fc-test-west-2 
--uuid out_chr_22

The relevant error reported when running the toil script is below,
and the larger output at:  http://pastebin.com/XP8wkBHk

The line of code causing the exception is in the bwa_alignment_code.py that I think John V wrote originally - so good to see if you have seen this before.  bwa does run for a while before this exception occurs.

