14275,IssuesEvent,2018-06-02 21:38:24+00:00,24043280,sshuttle/sshuttle,112729,brianmay,8774006,sshuttle,closed,systemd service never starts with Type=notify,[],[],2,"The documentation [recommends](https://sshuttle.readthedocs.io/en/stable/requirements.html#additional-suggested-software) using the `notify` mode if using a systemd service.

However in that case systemd waits for shuttle to send the notification which never happens and the service is killed because of the start timeout.

Using `Type=simple` in the service file fixes it.

I'm using the [official package on Arch Linux](https://www.archlinux.org/packages/community/any/sshuttle/).
Ironically, I am the one [who asked the Arch package maintainer](https://bugs.archlinux.org/task/56086) to implement the official `Type=notify` recommendation.",{},{}
14278,IssuesEvent,2016-09-04 19:35:19+00:00,24043280,sshuttle/sshuttle,7677524,lokeshh,8774006,sshuttle,opened,How to share sshuttle internet,[],[],0,"I cannot share my internet connection via hotspot that I got though sshuttle. Is there any way I can share the transparent internet I've got through a hotspot for my other devices such as Android?

