14536,IssuesEvent,2015-10-13 22:08:07+00:00,26516210,letsencrypt/letsencrypt,6504915,bmw,9289019,letsencrypt,closed,Suggestion for documentation format,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/labels/documentation', 'name': 'documentation', 'color': 'bfd4f2'}]",[],2,"For documentation down the road for Letsencrypt, would love something that lays out the client usage like https://sslmate.com/help/automation and https://sslmate.com/help/getting_started where it's formatted in a step by step basis structure which is end user task oriented.

You could break it down by

* native Ubuntu/Debian Apache 2.2/2.4 distro package install
* native Ubuntu/Debian Nginx distro package install
* CentOS/RHEL Apache distro package install
* CentOS/RHEL Nginx distro package install
* Other Apache source/custom installs
