15551,IssuesEvent,2017-12-21 16:01:06+00:00,6704888,django-import-export/django-import-export,1027694,zvolsky,12345453,django-import-export,opened,broken design in ul.object-tools,[],[],0,"The hack in
import_export/templates/admin/import_export/change_list.html
rewrites the ul.object-tools element.

However some admin template packages, especially bootstrap packages (I have tested django-admin-bootstrap and django-admin-bootstrapped) generate the same, but with additional classes like .pull-right.

In such case django-import-export will break their design
and in result the ul.object-tools can be completly hidden by other objects (and both Import and Add will be not accessible).

I know that this is completly ugly and the problem is somewhere between django standard admin, django admin template package and your project,
however I think you shoul remove your template completly and
a) let it so, because I don't feel that user without Add permissions should Import,
b) or, think about some other less conflicting solution - which will be difficult.

My meaning: a)

",{},{}
