15842,IssuesEvent,2018-07-12 16:08:20+00:00,51397392,pytroll/satpy,1828519,djhoese,13004956,pytroll,opened,Add ability to set output image size for `Scene.show`,"[{'id': 865017416, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw4NjUwMTc0MTY=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pytroll/satpy/labels/component:scene', 'name': 'component:scene', 'color': '1d76db', 'default': False}, {'id': 323805264, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwzMjM4MDUyNjQ=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pytroll/satpy/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 751601587, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw3NTE2MDE1ODc=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pytroll/satpy/labels/good%20first%20issue', 'name': 'good first issue', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': True}, {'id': 323805265, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwzMjM4MDUyNjU=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pytroll/satpy/labels/help%20wanted', 'name': 'help wanted', 'color': '159818', 'default': True}]",[],0,"**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
Using the show method in a jupyter notebook creates a PNG image that is the same size as the original dataset. Sometimes people want a small quicklook, not a complete full resolution representation of the data.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
Add a `size=None` keyword parameter that takes `(width, height)` tuple to specify the size of the output image. Not sure how exactly the resizing should be done (striding/slicing, Pillow method?, etc).

**Describe any changes to existing user workflow**
None. Optional new keyword argument.

**Additional python or other dependencies**
None.

**Describe any changes required to the build process**
No.

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
We could also add a `persist=False` keyword which would automatically call `persist()` on the dask array underneath a dataset before running it through the enhancement step so that any computations aren't wasted.

",{},{}
15869,IssuesEvent,2016-08-03 12:16:59+00:00,33873218,python-hyper/hpack,1382556,Lukasa,13035907,python-hyper,opened,"Limit total header block size, both inbound and outbound.",[],[],0,"Inspired by [section 4 of this document](http://www.imperva.com/docs/Imperva_HII_HTTP2.pdf), about the HPACK bomb.

HPACK can potentially use relatively little transmitted data to expand into a *substantial* amount of decompressed data. We should resist this attack by limiting the maximum size of the output header block to some reasonable (user-configurable) number, and defaulting it sensibly: probably to 16kB in the first instance.",{},{}
