I have a rectangle in a color image and I wanna get this rectangle for the depth image. Now I use **_rs2::align_** object with **_process_** method. But it is very costly (probably because this method align all image while I need only 4 pixels). Is it possible to find coordinates of a rectangle got for a color image in the corresponding depth image? (maybe using intrinsic/extrinsic). I had an idea to transform color pixel corrdinates to 3D color coordinates then to 3D depth coordinate and finnaly this 3D depth coordinates to 2D depth coordinates. But it seems impossible to get 3D color points from 2D color points because the **_rs2_deproject_pixel_to_point(float point[3], const struct rs2_intrinsics * intrin, const float pixel[2], float depth)_** function needs the depth parameter.
