16386,IssuesEvent,2016-09-11 04:22:50+00:00,43056951,graphql-python/graphene,188257,syrusakbary,15002022,graphql-python,closed,Querying filter args on a DjangoFilterConnectionField returning full (unfiltered) results,[],[],2,"Hey guys,

I'm using `v1.0.dev`. I have a `DjangoObjectType` that has some `filter_fields` defined on the `Meta`. This object type is set up on the query as a `DjangoFilterConnectionField`. The arguments on the query are set up correctly so you can post queries using the filter_fields but the result is the full list unfiltered.

I also tried implementing a custom `django_filter.FilterSet` class but it doesn't work either.

## How to reproduce

```python
# models.py
# ...
class Post(models.Model):
    text = models.TextField()


# schema.py
# ...
class PostType(DjangoObjectType):
    class Meta:
        interfaces = (relay.Node,)
        model = Post
        filter_fields = {
            'text': ['icontains']
        }

class Query(graphene.ObjectType):
    posts = DjangoFilterConnectionField(PostType)


# test.py
# ...
Post.objects.create(text='Try to filter this')
Post.objects.create(text='Try to filter that')
Post.objects.create(text='But not this')

query_string = """"""
{
  posts(text_Icontains: ""filter"") {
    edges{node{text}}}
}
""""""
schema = graphene.Schema(query=Query)
result = schema.execute(query_string)

assert len(result['posts']['edges']) == 2
```",{},{}
