16630,IssuesEvent,2016-09-09 03:03:32+00:00,55808787,openthread/openthread,20312411,chshu,16142269,openthread,closed,Device can't rejoin network after hardware reset,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/openthread/openthread/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'cc317c'}]",[],8,"In a formed OpenThread network, if one device run into a hardware reset (all the parameters will be reset), the device can not rejoin the network again due to `Frame Counter` mismatch, then it will become a leader and form a new partition, and will go through a partition merging process.

Not sure if it is as design, or a potential issue needs to be fixed? And I failed to find any corresponding description in specification talking about this case (rejoin after hardware reset). Appreciate for any feedbacks, thanks.",{},{}
