16675,IssuesEvent,2017-09-05 13:28:19+00:00,32363483,python-escpos/python-escpos,5815815,devdevnullnull,16302939,python-escpos,closed,Printer Unresponsive,[],[],2,"I have:
- [x] searched open and closed issues for duplicates

### Bug description
I've install both the development version cloning the repo and the stable one (in different enviroments). I'm using an epson stylus c63. The printer is correctly detected o both oses, and I've also got some info from the printer (paper status for example).
I've tested own code, some examples of the ""examples"" directory and the example of the README.md. No error is outputed, only unresponsivness from the printer. 
Since there is no error, is hard to know where is the problem. And since de printer is correctly detected by the library, is hard to know if it is actually supported (according to the ESC/P manual, it is...)

",{},{}
16676,IssuesEvent,2016-03-09 10:39:11+00:00,32363483,python-escpos/python-escpos,4189642,patkan,16302939,python-escpos,opened,version number for new release,[],[],0,"I plan to do a release with all our fixes in the near future.

Which version number should we use?
The last version number here is `1.0.9` in order to avoid confusion with https://pypi.python.org/pypi/python-escpos/1.0.10 we should at least take something bigger than `1.0.10`.

I would take 1.1.0 since we had quite a lot of changes. I think incrementing the major version is unnecessary since I am not aware of any API changes that break behaviour.

What do you think?",{},{}
