17371,IssuesEvent,2017-10-18 03:20:26+00:00,56792799,mozilla-releng/scriptworker,826343,escapewindow,19614164,mozilla-releng,closed,bug 1407380 - Add error message on python crash,"[{'id': 362041705, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla-releng/scriptworker/labels/help%20wanted', 'name': 'help wanted', 'color': '128A0C', 'default': True}]",[],0,"At [this line](https://github.com/mozilla-releng/scriptworker/blob/46f913f/scriptworker/task.py#L175-L177), we print `""exit code: {}"".format(exitcode)` to the logfile.

In [bug 1398800](https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1398800), we're hitting a lot of `exit code: -11`. This is an issue we need to address elsewhere, but in the meantime, we can add an informative error message that will be more easily spotted.

Let's do something like

```
if exitcode == -11:
    status_line = ""Automation Error: python exited with signal {}"".format(exitcode)
```

before the `log.info` and `print` at the bottom of that block.",{},{}
