17906,IssuesEvent,2018-01-22 19:08:38+00:00,68402336,streamlink/streamlink,1396878,gravyboat,22243823,streamlink,closed,Build a package and get it upstreamed into Debian,"[{'id': 443888410, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/streamlink/streamlink/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 443888411, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/streamlink/streamlink/labels/help%20wanted', 'name': 'help wanted', 'color': '128A0C', 'default': True}, {'id': 443888413, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/streamlink/streamlink/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'cc317c', 'default': True}]",[],19,"Currently livestreamer is available as a package which can be easily installed on Debian/Ubuntu, this is not the case for streamlink. If we want to get this packaged up and ready for the next release we need to move quickly. as @javiercantero mentions [here]https://github.com/chrippa/livestreamer/issues/1427#issuecomment-249653892) they'll be freezing the the release in the beginning of January. While I'm familiar with building RPMs and am okay at building debs I'm not very familiar with building debs that go into the upstream repo. If we have anyone who is an expert working on the project I would love to get your help with this. I don't think we'll be able to get this sort of coverage (http://docs.livestreamer.io/install.html#linux-and-bsd-packages), but having it be available for at least Debian and Ubuntu would be nice.

There is some existing stuff related to the builds that chrippa put in place (https://packages.debian.org/sid/video/livestreamer), but I think we'll have to do some clean up to get everything prepared.

 Is this something that we want to do? Or should we wait on a package till we've rebuilt the CLI, then hope we can get it in at a later date?
",{},{}
