18023,IssuesEvent,2018-01-08 22:21:47+00:00,76196733,goose3/goose3,327544,Enkerli,24511568,goose3,opened,Strange Behaviour from `known_context_patterns`,[],[],0,"As per an exchange with @barrust on a [Python-Goose issue](https://github.com/grangier/python-goose/issues/270) (in Python2), here’s a strange issue from using `known_context_patterns`.

This code fails, and throws a 404 (traceback at the end):
````
from goose3 import Goose
g = Goose()
# g.config.known_context_patterns = {'attr': 'class', 'value': 'datos_caso'}
# g.config.known_context_patterns = {'attr': 'class', 'value': 'pr-xs-20'}
article = g.extract(url='http://www.incyde.org/casos-exito/1')
print(article.cleaned_text)
````

Uncommenting line 3, it produces this (which isn’t too far from the appropriate result):

> Programa de ""Tengo una Idea"" (UCAM - 2015)
> Programa de ""Social Media Networker"" (UCAM - 2015)

Sounds weird that the `known_context_patterns` would make such a difference. Guess part of the difference is that, when the parser isn’t specifically searching for `datos_caso`, it trips over an image, maybe?

Other pages from the same site produce different results (can’t find a class to consistently get results from those). For instance, the root of that same path (`http://www.incyde.org/casos-exito`) produces appropriate results using the pattern in line 4 (`g.config.known_context_patterns = {'attr': 'class', 'value': 'pr-xs-20'}`):

> ""Desde que entré en el programa de formación de Fundación Incyde y El ITM de Murcia para emprendedores, todo ha resultado mucho más fácil. He recibido formación de profesionales del sector del marketing online que han sido muy productivos 

...

Without the patterns, it has issues with cookies:

>Uso de cookies: Utilizamos cookies propias y de terceros para mejorar su experiencia y nuestros servicios, analizando la navegación en nuestro sitio web. Si continua navegando, consideramos que acepta su uso. Puede obtener más información en nuestra política de cookies.

Applying both patterns to individual pages (`http://www.incyde.org/casos-exito/1`) produces the same 404.

More specifically, this:
````
from goose3 import Goose
g = Goose()
g.config.known_context_patterns = {'attr': 'class', 'value': 'datos_caso'}
g.config.known_context_patterns = {'attr': 'class', 'value': 'pr-xs-20'}
article = g.extract(url='http://www.incyde.org/casos-exito/1')
print(article.cleaned_text)
````

produces the same Traceback as this:
````
from goose3 import Goose
g = Goose()
# g.config.known_context_patterns = {'attr': 'class', 'value': 'datos_caso'}
# g.config.known_context_patterns = {'attr': 'class', 'value': 'pr-xs-20'}
article = g.extract(url='http://www.incyde.org/casos-exito/1')
print(article.cleaned_text)
````

But this works:
````
from goose3 import Goose
g = Goose()
g.config.known_context_patterns = {'attr': 'class', 'value': 'datos_caso'}
# g.config.known_context_patterns = {'attr': 'class', 'value': 'pr-xs-20'}
article = g.extract(url='http://www.incyde.org/casos-exito/1')
print(article.cleaned_text)
````

The traceback:
````
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""incydecasos1.py"", line 5, in <module>
